==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Atramentarious
<hw>At`ra*men*ta"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>atramentaire</ets>. See <er>Atramentaceous</er>.]</ety> <def>Like
ink; suitable for making ink. Sulphate of iron (copperas, green vitriol)
is called <xex>atramentarious</xex>, as being used in making
ink.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

